{
  "stem": "17426.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 264.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so we come to the conclusion that it wasn't only the SS that was destroying the European Jewry.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was every German who lent his hand to function in behalf of the [? pogrom. ?]",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Dobra ghetto was not surrounded by barbed wire.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was surround-- it-- it had a per se order that we cannot go out of this particular perimeter, but there was no fence.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, and I still have some of it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A yellow Star of David with the word 'Jude' on if, and the letter spelling 'Jude' was sort of a abstract Hebrew letters, which was even more painful.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had to attach it to the front in the left-hand side, approximate in the area of the heart, and in the rear, in the same area of the heart.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My sister and I decided to go to Russia, decided to smuggle to Russia.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we decided one day, and we left very early in the morning.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was still dark.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we made it as far as the railroad station.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At the railroad station we were caught as Jews, and we were told to go back and never do it again because the next time we'll be shot.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so we came back to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was the most difficult part because we were left sort of to a minimum of perhaps 300 or 400 or 500 calories a day in terms of what the Judenstaat could deliver to us.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "To substitute for the need that we were deprived of, we have traded our goods.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We traded our personal things that we have.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If anyone had some jewelry, he traded that to Poles that used to come to the ghetto or outside the ghetto in certain spots where they felt secure enough.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
